replace function
The <b>replace function</b> replaces all occurences of some substring inside a
larger string:
<pre>
>>> some_string = 'She sells seashells on the sea shore'
>>> print some_string.replace('sea', 'bay')
She sells bayshells on the bay shore
>>> grocery_list = 'eggs milk bread bananas and sugar'
>>> print grocery_list.replace(' ', ',')
eggs,milk,bread,bananas,and,sugar
